# Adjudication Engine — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

**Layer 10 — Adjudication Engine** per §2.10. Resolves conflicts from the synthesis layer using authority weighting, agreement scoring, and a re-verification loop.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    CC["Conflict Candidates"] --> CONTRA["Semantic Contradiction<br/>Score ≤ 0.30 → confirmed"]
    CONTRA -->|"confirmed"| AUTH["Authority Weighting<br/>6-component formula"]
    CONTRA -->|"not confirmed"| PASS["Both claims coexist"]
    AUTH --> AGREE["Agreement Scoring<br/>workers supporting / total"]
    AGREE --> RECHECK{"Clear winner?<br/>&gt;5% margin"}
    RECHECK -->|"Yes"| WIN["Accept winner<br/>Reject loser"]
    RECHECK -->|"No"| LOOP{"Round &lt; 2?"}
    LOOP -->|"Yes"| CONTRA
    LOOP -->|"No"| UNRES["Unresolved<br/>Use highest weighted<br/>Reduce confidence"]
    WIN --> RESULT["AdjudicationResult"]
    UNRES --> RESULT
    PASS --> RESULT
```

